[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = MTH229Lite","category":"page"},{"location":"#MTH229Lite","page":"Home","title":"MTH229Lite","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for MTH229Lite.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [MTH229Lite]","category":"page"},{"location":"#MTH229Lite.annotate!-Tuple{Plot, Any, Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"MTH229Lite.annotate!","text":"annotate!([p::Plot], x, y, txt; size, color, textposition, kwargs...)\nannotate!([p::Plot], anns::Tuple; size, color, textposition, kwargs...)\n\nAdd annotations to plot\n\nsize: text size\ncolor: text color\ntextposition: one of \"top\", \"bottom\", \"left\", \"right\", or combinations with _\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#MTH229Lite.plot!-Tuple{Plot, Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"MTH229Lite.plot!","text":"plot!([p::Plot], f; kwargs...)\nplot!([p::Plot], x, y; kwargs...)\n\nUsed to add a new tract to an existing plot. Like Plots.plot!\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#MTH229Lite.plot-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"MTH229Lite.plot","text":"plot(x, y; kwargs...)\nplot(f::Function, a, b; kwargs...)\n\nCreate a plot. Returns a Plot instance from PlotlyLight\n\nProvides an interface like Plots.plot for plotting a function f using PlotlyLight. This just scratches the surface, but PlotLight allows full acces to the underlying JavaScript library.\n\nThe provided \"Plots\" like functions are plot, plot!, scatter, scatter!, annotate, annotate!, title!.\n\nExample\n\nplot(sin, 0, 2pi)\nplot!(cos)\nx0 = [pi/4, 5pi/4]\nscatter!(x0, sin.(x0), markersize=10)\ntitle!(\"Sine and cosine and where they intersect in [0,2π]\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#MTH229Lite.plotif-NTuple{4, Any}","page":"Home","title":"MTH229Lite.plotif","text":"plotif(f, g, a, b)\n\nPlot f colored depending on g >= 0 or not.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#MTH229Lite.scatter-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"MTH229Lite.scatter","text":"scatter(x, y; markershape, markercolor, markersize, kwargs...)\nscatter!([p::Plot], x, y; kwargs...)\n\nPlace point on a plot.\n\nmarkershape: shape, e.g. \"diamond\" or \"diamond-open\"\nmarkercolor: color e.g. \"red\"\nmarkersize:  size, as an integer\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#MTH229Lite.title!-Tuple{Plot, Any}","page":"Home","title":"MTH229Lite.title!","text":"title!([p::Plot], txt)\n\nSet plot title.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
